{"id":6692,"date":"2015-12-12T00:04:56","date_gmt":"2015-12-12T07:04:56","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/?p=6692"},"modified":"2019-04-23T17:37:24","modified_gmt":"2019-04-23T23:37:24","slug":"top-dressing-decorative-rocks","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/top-dressing-decorative-rocks\/","title":{"rendered":"Top Dressing: Decorative rocks for your succulents"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p><em>Learn how to add a professional touch to your succulent arrangements by using a top dressing, or decorative rocks. This simple addition will take your succulents to a whole new level!<\/em><\/p>\n<p>One of my favorite discoveries in regard to designing with succulents is the use of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/bonsai_succulent_top_dressingsas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">top dressings<\/a>. If you're not familiar with this term, a top dressing is simply decorative rocks that are placed on top of the soil after your arrangement is set.<\/p>\n<p>This often overlooked feature can make a beautiful arrangement even more stunning.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6693\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/What-a-good-idea-Using-a-top-dressing-really-makes-a-succulent-arrangement-look-more-professional-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"What a good idea! Using a top dressing for succulents really makes an arrangement look more professional!\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p>My friends Michael and Danielle Romero were the first to introduce me to this idea. They are amazing designers and I was fortunate to photograph some of their arrangements when working on my book, <em><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1NhhgJv\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Idiot's Guides: Succulents<\/a><\/em>.<\/p>\n<p>When I arrived to photograph, they were just finishing up adding the top dressings to several succulent arrangements. It was so amazing to see the transformation of these arrangements as they carefully selected top dressings to coordinate with their succulents.<\/p>\n<p>This combination of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=topdressing_ghost&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F152796820%2Fsucculent-plant-graptopetalum%3Fga_order%3Dmost_relevant%26ga_search_type%3Dall%26ga_view_type%3Dgallery%26ga_search_query%3Dghost%2520plant%2520succulent%26ref%3Dsr_gallery_3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Graptoveria\u00a0paraguayense<\/a> with the purple top dressing in a purple pot was my favorite.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6702\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Stunning-arrangement-with-Graptoveria-paraguayense-and-a-dark-purple-top-dressing-with-a-geode-accent-rock-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Stunning arrangement with Graptoveria paraguayense and a dark purple top dressing with a geode accent rock\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I also loved these crazy <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=topdressing_baby&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F115851491%2Fsucculent-plant-crassula-babys-necklace%3Fga_order%3Dmost_relevant%26ga_search_type%3Dall%26ga_view_type%3Dgallery%26ga_search_query%3Dbaby%2520necklace%2520succulent%26ref%3Dsr_gallery_3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Crassula\u00a0marnieriana<\/a> with a simple pink and grey pea gravel as the top dressing.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6695\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Crassula-marnieriana-witha-simple-gravel-top-dressing-that-mimics-its-colors-585x390.jpg\" alt=\"Crassula marnieriana witha simple gravel top dressing that mimics it's colors\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" \/><\/p>\n<p>There are many benefits to using a top dressing! Watch the video below for more information.<\/p>\n<div class=\"video-responsive\"><iframe src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/cxJOFP5G0hs?rel=0&showinfo=0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"><\/iframe><\/div>\n<p>Adding a top dressing to your succulent arrangement is so simple.<\/p>\n<p>After you've filled the pot with soil and plants, just pour the top dressing right on top of the soil.<\/p>\n<p>Using these <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1NUsukd\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">tweezers and bead scoop<\/a> are helpful for small spaces. See the difference a top dressing made with this <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=topdressing_lola&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F92302884%2Fsucculent-plant-echeveria-lola%3Fga_order%3Dmost_relevant%26ga_search_type%3Dall%26ga_view_type%3Dgallery%26ga_search_query%3Dlola%2520succulent%26ref%3Dsr_gallery_6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Echeveria &#8216;Lola'<\/a>?<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6697\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Echeveria-Lola-potted-without-a-top-dressing-585x585.jpg\" alt=\"Echeveria Lola potted without a top dressing\" width=\"585\" height=\"585\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6696\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Echeveria-Lola-potted-with-a-light-pastel-top-dressing-from-Bonsai-Jack-585x585.jpg\" alt=\"Echeveria Lola potted with a light pastel top dressing from Bonsai Jack\" width=\"585\" height=\"585\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Adding these decorative rocks not only looks good, but it's functional too! The top dressing help keeps the soil in place when watering.<\/p>\n<p>This prevents the arrangement from shifting very much over time. It can also reduce the amount of dust that flies up when you water.<\/p>\n<p>Watch the video below to see the difference adding a top dressing can make when you're cleaning up a succulent arrangement!<\/p>\n<div class=\"video-responsive\"><iframe src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/dqfWKJQP2-I?rel=0&showinfo=0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"><\/iframe><\/div>\n<p>While I loved this idea of using top dressings, I was surprised at how difficult it was to find a top dressing for succuelnts I loved that was easy to purchase. I've spent hours shopping online and locally for just the right thing.<\/p>\n<p>When I couldn't find quite what I was looking for, I reached out to the fabulous Bonsai Jack for help. Sure enough, he was able to add a line of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/bonsai_succulent_top_dressingsas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">top dressings<\/a> to his store!<\/p>\n<p>We came up with seven\u00a0different color options to choose from. I'm partial to the light pastel myself, but there are options from light to dark so you'll find something you love!<\/p>\n<p>The options include: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/bonsai_succulent_top_dressingsas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\">light pastel, dark pastel, earth tone, gold, black lava, maroon lava, and pumice (white)<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h3>Light Pastel<\/h3>\n<p>Here is an arrangement I made with the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/bonsai_succulent_top_dressingsas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">light pastel top dressing<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=topdressing_sunset&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F130831174%2Fsucculent-plant-graptosedum-california%3Fga_order%3Dmost_relevant%26ga_search_type%3Dall%26ga_view_type%3Dgallery%26ga_search_query%3Dcalifornia%2520sunset%2520succulent%26ref%3Dsr_gallery_2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Graptoveria &#8216;California Sunset'<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=topdressing_rupestris&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F257880048%2Fcrassula-rupestris-succulent-25%3Fga_order%3Dmost_relevant%26ga_search_type%3Dall%26ga_view_type%3Dgallery%26ga_search_query%3Dcrassula%2520rupestris%26ref%3Dsr_gallery_3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Crassula rupestris<\/a>, and a bonsai pot from <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=topdressing_hamazo&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2Fhamazo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Hamazo<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6699\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Graptoveria-California-Sunset-and-Crassula-rupestris-with-a-light-pastel-top-dressing-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Graptoveria California Sunset and Crassula rupestris with a light pastel top dressing\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I've photographed a few of the top dressing options from Bonsai Jack and included them below.<\/p>\n<p>By the way&#8230; if you buy two bags of top dressings from him you can get the second one half off with code &#8220;topdressing&#8221;. Such a great deal!<\/p>\n<h3>Dark Pastel<\/h3>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6694\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/A-stunning-combination-of-succulents-with-a-coordinating-top-dressing-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"A stunning combination of succulents with a coordinating top dressing\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>Earth Tone<\/h3>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6698\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Echeveria-Neon-Breakers-with-an-earth-tone-top-dressing-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Echeveria Neon Breakers with an earth tone top dressing\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>Gold<\/h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_6701\" style=\"width: 745px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-6701\" class=\"wp-image-6701 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Stunning-Sedum-nussbaumerianum-with-Crassula-lycopodioides-and-a-gold-gravel-top-dressing.jpg\" alt=\"Stunning Sedum nussbaumerianum with Crassula lycopodioides and a gold gravel top dressing\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Stunning-Sedum-nussbaumerianum-with-Crassula-lycopodioides-and-a-gold-gravel-top-dressing-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Stunning-Sedum-nussbaumerianum-with-Crassula-lycopodioides-and-a-gold-gravel-top-dressing-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/Stunning-Sedum-nussbaumerianum-with-Crassula-lycopodioides-and-a-gold-gravel-top-dressing.jpg 735w\" 